rComments: Do not agree with any of the comments on here. The material was more challenging than any of my other classes at Ottawa U, or in my undergrad. There is room for flexibility according to student needs; which reflects the academic material covered in class. Never met a more engaging, enthusiastic, and helpful Professor, who actually cares.
very friendly and tries to be helpful, but teaches university class like it is a group of kindergarten kids.

Very energetic, kind. Changes the course outline and course requirements about once a week.The week before handing in our last assignment she once again changed her expectations. She is very unclear as to what she wants. Too much group work, lectures are irrelevant.  She spent an entire class presenting her own research and talking about herself
Very enthusiastic, brings alot of excitement to class! Perfect suitability with the type of class! Really enjoyed the class!

Absolutely brutal, although energetic and excited she cannot convey the teacher material correctly. It couldnt be more ironic that a person teaching "Teaching Strategies in Physical Activity" is a terrible teacher.
Well, she is energetic but that's about it.

Really lively and outgoing prof. She loves what she does and tries to motivate everyone. Unfortunatly it's extremely difficult to understand what the course is about half the time, wording is difficult to comprehend. Textbook is also ABSOLUTELY brutal to read, but necessary. Exams are easy-moderate though, her marking is very fair if not easy.
